Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.63,0:14:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let go of clutching and grasping.\NClarify your goals and your ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.88,0:14:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that all value is or arbitrary.\NAll value is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.68,0:15:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What value you add to a thing is\Nuh an arbitrary selection.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.63,0:15:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you're rich and famous or\Nwhether you're poor and humble, in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.88,0:15:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,end it's all the same because all value\Nis arbitrary. All you can buy in the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.56,0:15:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,meantime is comfort and style.\NComfort and style.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.19,0:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a map on a train\Nof a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.19,0:15:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,on the train.\NA train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.51,0:15:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A train for a plane.\N>> I got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.60,0:15:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Being happy means that you take a nap\Nwhen you're on a train or a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.88,0:15:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember being grounded for six hours\Nin Greece one time. They're having air
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.92,0:16:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,maneuvers of the military. So we got\Ngrounded for six hours. Six hours on the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.92,0:16:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,ground was very boring.\NSo happily after half an hour I fell
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,asleep.\NBut six hours sitting there frantically
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.95,0:16:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to push time. Huh. Okay. a nap on\Na plane or a train.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.80,0:16:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Live one day at a time. That is\Ncertainly part of the 12step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.75,0:16:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday is over and tomorrow never\Ncomes. You realize that tomorrow never
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.48,0:16:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,comes because tomorrow it'll it'll be\Nthe next day will be tomorrow. So
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.12,0:16:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,live one day at a time.\NHappiness is in the small things of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.83,0:16:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,life. the sound of a kitty's purr or a\Ndog's wagging tail. I mean, what could
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,be happier than hear a purr kitty? So,\Nour kitties in the morning, I got three
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.95,0:16:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of them on the bed. They're going\Npurr purr. Three of them are doing that
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.48,0:17:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same timer.\NAnd then the dog comes around and puts
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,her nose over the top of the bed to make\Nsure that all three kitties are where
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.76,0:17:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,they're supposed to be.\Nher dog, she's a hurting dog. So her job
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is to make sure all kitties are where\Nthey're supposed to be. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so just living with animal life, I\Nthink, is very beneficial. And as I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.55,0:17:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,said, I used to have patients who lived\Nalone and were depressed. And I told
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.40,0:17:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,them, unless you get a dog, I can't\Ntreat you because otherwise you're just
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.67,0:17:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,egoentrically\Nconcerned about yourself all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.36,0:17:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, me, me, me. And uh having a pet of\Nany kind or a canary or a bird or a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.88,0:17:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,kitty or a doggy, you start thinking\Nabout something other than yourself. Is
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.16,0:17:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the doggy comfortable? Did the doggy\Nhave his dinner? Did the doggy go out?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.24,0:17:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, you're thinking about another\Nliving thing and its happiness and its
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.64,0:18:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,success.\NOkay. Happiness is a kitty's purr or a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.16,0:18:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,dog's wagging tail.\NI used to have a monkey and the monkey
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.12,0:18:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a kinkaju. A kinkaju is a\NSouth American honey bear and I had it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.72,0:18:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in a cage hanging over a bathtub in some\Nplace I lived. And the kinkaju's uh fur
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.76,0:18:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,got dull and his eyes got dull and he\Nlost his appetite.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So intuition hit me. So I went out and I\Nbought a monkey and I hunked in the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.91,0:18:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,monkey in a cage over the bathtub and\Nanother hook. So here was the kinkaju
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.52,0:18:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,here and the monkey there and they hated\Neach other.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.67,0:18:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The king of Jew hated the monkey and the\Nmonkey would throw things at the king
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.16,0:18:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but the king of Jew's fur got shiny and\Nglossy and his eyes sparkled and he was
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.79,0:18:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,quite happy.\NSo my intuition was right and so the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.08,0:19:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness is a is to be related to other\Nliving things and uh to love the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.03,0:19:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,as you go through the woods to love your\Ngarden as you love. So faith versus
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.08,0:19:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,skepticism\Ngratitude for what you have and have
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.64,0:19:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,become\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.55,0:19:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it's better to be detached than to crave\Nthings. People, some people think if you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.84,0:19:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,want a thing, it's because you don't\Ncrave it one enough. And instead, the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.32,0:19:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is to become lighthearted,\Nlighthearted about it and detached. If
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.20,0:19:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you w the lottery, you win it. And if\Nyou don't, you don't. But if you get
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.52,0:19:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,hung up and craving to win the lottery,\Neven if you win it, your life's going to
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.84,0:19:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,be horrible.\NThere's stories on television. The lives
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.84,0:19:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who have won the lottery,\Nevery one of them was a disaster. I
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.67,0:19:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,think the divorce rate was 100% suicide\Nrate
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.00,0:19:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and these are the people who became\Ninstant millionaires
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:20:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the whether the world is glass is\Nhalf full or it's half empty. So that's
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.24,0:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,optimism versus pessimism.\NSo if you're not too far along in life,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be grateful and say, "Thank God I've got\Nplenty of room to grow and gain and lots
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.44,0:20:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of pleasure to look forward to." If\Nyou're already rich and famous and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.36,0:20:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,happy, you haven't got too much left,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.08,0:20:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can get a bad cold and wish go\Noptimist versus pessimist
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.52,0:20:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and to have spiritual rather than\Nmaterial gains. It isn't the material
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.44,0:20:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,gain. It's the spiritual significance\Nthat God has seen to it that you are
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.64,0:20:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,well provided for.\Nuh is like by good karma and grace. So
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.20,0:20:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful that we have what we need\Nto live life in a satisfactory manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.96,0:21:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Okay.\NLive one day at a time. This is again
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.40,0:21:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the 12step program. Uh yep.\NDetach versus craven glass half full.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.52,0:21:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual versus material goals. Okay.\NWhat's the next slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.67,0:21:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there another one?\NIs there another slide?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.28,0:21:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is there another slide waiting for us?\N>> Oh boy. Oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.67,0:21:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Good for us.\NGood for us. We made it through all the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.08,0:21:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,slides.\NThat's my main ambition when I got up
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.15,0:21:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning.\NDear God, please help us get through all
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.08,0:21:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the slides.\N>> What? A new one. We're not done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.96,0:22:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> We're not done.\N>> All right. It must be God's will that we
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.40,0:22:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,have another\Nslide to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.28,0:22:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender to God's will.\NThe capacity to let go to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.20,0:22:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering to God's will is is\Nsuccessfully letting go of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.96,0:22:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of thinking that you have to\Ndo a certain thing that you must do a
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.72,0:22:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,certain thing and seeing to it that\Nhowever it goes is going to be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.40,0:22:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity. So the learning how to let go\Nthen anybody knows how to grasp and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.64,0:22:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,grab. Everybody knows that. Even an\Nidiot knows how to grasp. But to know
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.55,0:22:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,when to let go is something else. Huh.\N>> You might mention we're doing a book on
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.15,0:22:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\N>> We're doing a book on letting go. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.48,0:22:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the name of the book. In fact,\Nlet go. Yeah. How to let go. Because
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.36,0:23:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then you drop the book. You let go of\Nthe book.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.55,0:23:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I let go of the book and it's on the\Nfloor now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.12,0:23:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, because uh society drives us in\Nthe other direction, we learn the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.91,0:23:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual technique of uh letting a\Nthing go, surrendering it, and uh open
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.36,0:23:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your hand and let it. So, we want to be\Npleased with our progress wherever we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.55,0:23:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are. You don't have to become a Buddha\Nnow. And uh you may never become a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.72,0:23:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha. And uh Buddha, last time I spoke\Nto him, says, "I don't really need any
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.08,0:23:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,help.\NOnce you're detached from the world, you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.91,0:23:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,don't really need much help." Okay? You\Nwant to avoid self- judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.15,0:23:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, where am I? Am I being good?\NAm I being bad? etc. That doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.12,0:24:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,becoming unconscious.\NSelf-aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.88,0:24:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So become self-aware rather than\Nself-judgmental.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.08,0:24:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that the terms good and bad are\Nall circumstantial.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.64,0:24:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Good as compared to what? Bad as\Ncompared to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.08,0:24:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Realize that in life winning is\Nprovisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.20,0:24:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is only temporary. Winning is\Nhow you ever define it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.32,0:24:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning is not desiring fame or money.\NHow's that? That way you can be piss
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.36,0:24:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,poor and win.\NTake vows of poverty. The less money you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.44,0:24:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,have, the better you're doing.\NAll right. Winning is a is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.79,0:25:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's however you define it. And the\Nshortest avenue is through simplicity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.08,0:25:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than complexity. Yes. All right.\NRealistic expectations of yourself and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.15,0:25:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the world\Nand uh realistic expectations of what is
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.55,0:25:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,common in human consciousness.\NWe would like our governing body to be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.27,0:25:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,better than it is. We would like our\Npoliticians to be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.67,0:25:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody and his brother should be\Ndoing a better job.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.52,0:25:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If it was possible, uh, it would be so.\NValue is in the eye of the beholder. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.96,0:25:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever you think is valuable out there\Nis a projection. So, that's similar to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.24,0:25:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole concept about glamour.\NThe g value which you know glamour is in
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.88,0:25:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the eye of the beholder.\NIf you think it's wonderful and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.55,0:26:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,valuable, it'd be great. My father had a\Ngreat big heavy gold ring with a great
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.76,0:26:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,big amethyst in it. He just loved that\Nring. And he was a piano player. So he'd
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.20,0:26:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,play the piano and here it' be this big\Ngold ring with this big amethyst. He
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.03,0:26:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just loved he loved the amethyst stone,\Nyou know, and he wanted to leave it to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.00,0:26:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,me.\NI said, "Dad, I'm never going to wear
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.88,0:26:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that.\Na big gold ring that weighs a quarter of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.96,0:26:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a pound for God's sake with a big\Namethyst.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.60,0:26:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "I hate to decline it, but I'm\Nnever gonna wear it." Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.79,0:26:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the value is in the eye of the\Nbeholder. Just like
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.08,0:26:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,give up skepticism.\NGive up skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.88,0:26:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a sense of humor.\NIt's hard to beat anybody who has a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.91,0:26:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sense of humor because no matter what\Nyou do, it appears comical because how
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.12,0:27:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you hold it in mind is what creates the\Nsense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.55,0:27:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Accepting karmic propensity, in other\Nwords, if things are not going your way,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.44,0:27:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you say, well, uh, it could be well be a\Nreason for that. People who do past life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.55,0:27:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,regression often find what the karmic\Npropensity was and it makes it extremely
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.88,0:27:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,acceptable.\NYou know what what happened in that what
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.55,0:27:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,lifetime and what you did about it and\Nuh one time I was having surgery relying
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.55,0:27:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anesthesia and in the middle of it I\Nwent back to that lifetime and I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.96,0:27:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,good God what did I ever do and suddenly\NI like relived it. I actually like
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.00,0:27:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,relived what had happened and I think\NI've told that story before and uh I was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.96,0:27:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a warrior and I profoundly wounded my\Nenemy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.24,0:27:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead of killing him I left him\Nthere to die of his wounds
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.88,0:28:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and in this lifetime I then had to go\Nthrough ingal surgery without anesthesia
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.55,0:28:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and during that surgery I thought\Nkarmically I must have done something to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.08,0:28:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,warrant this and I did I did not give\Nhim the cudigra. I left him to die of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.44,0:28:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,his wounds. So the code of the warrior\Nis to finish off your opponent if he's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.72,0:28:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to finish himself off. And I\Ndidn't have the moral courage to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.60,0:28:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or wasn't trained enough to realize that\Nwas my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.91,0:28:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When he's laying there crippled and and\Nhorribly wounded, you say to the guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.24,0:28:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"You want to leave?" And the guy says,\N"Yeah, you let him leave." If he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.52,0:28:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"No, I'll stay." You let him stay.\NA severely wounded warrior does not say,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.32,0:28:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"I think I'll stay except once in a\Ngreat while."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.79,0:28:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Give up skepticism. Have a\Nsense of humor. Accept karmic
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.79,0:28:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,propensities. See essence rather than\Nperception.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.36,0:28:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the inner core reality that this\Nthing represents?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.72,0:29:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't reject a diamond just\Nbecause it's a diamond because the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.55,0:29:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,diamond could well be, you know, a\Nkeepsake left to you by your mother. So
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.44,0:29:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of that diamond is not the\Nmonetary value of the diamond, but the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.52,0:29:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that it was your mother's and\Nshe wore it during her whole life. So
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.24,0:29:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you want to see the essence of a thing\Nrather than the story that you project
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.96,0:29:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,onto it. and jocular instead of morose.\NTo be humorous and see the funny side of
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.39,0:29:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,everything\Nis uplifting.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.24,0:29:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's hard to be serious.\NIn the middle of very serious things, I
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.76,0:29:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have to watch myself.\NYou have to watch yourself because
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.72,0:29:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you've taken a more lighthearted view\Ninstead of being heavy heavyhearted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.20,0:30:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there any more on this one? This\Nslide, honey. Is there more? Hey,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.64,0:30:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,good will regarding all of life. That's\Nthe most important one of all, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.24,0:30:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To be of good will towards all of life\Nand all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.44,0:30:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Of goodwill towards the woods as you\Nwalk through the woods. of the little
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.08,0:30:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,bugs that you try to step around so you\Ndon't squish them. Of good will towards
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.12,0:30:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody.\NGood will regarding all of life in all
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.00,0:30:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of its expressions. To love life as life\Nas an expression of divinity. So one can
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.36,0:30:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,see life is the radiance of divinity and\Nit it's good you know a good thing to
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.32,0:30:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,love and guard and and cherish to be\Neasygoing rather than rigid if it
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.32,0:30:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't work this way you let it go that\Nway
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.32,0:30:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a person will say but the ego\Nsays isn't that being wishywashy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.32,0:31:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,wishywashy\NI'd rather be wishy-washy and and
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.91,0:31:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightened than tough minded and going\Nto hell eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.84,0:31:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Reduce expectations of yourself and\Nothers. If you find a seat on the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.48,0:31:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,subway, so much the better. Yeah. Yeah.\NI like that story of the of uh the woman
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.15,0:31:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in in the subway and she says this\Ngentleman's sitting in the seat. She
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.64,0:31:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "Would you mind giving your your\Nseat to a pregnant woman, expectant
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.20,0:31:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,mother?" "Oh, no." He said, "No." He\Nlooked at her. She looks at her as slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.72,0:31:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, "How long you been pregnant?"\NShe says, "Oh, about an hour and a half.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.27,0:31:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Be gracious to yourself and to others.\NSurrender the need to control." That's
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.88,0:31:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the biggest one I think that people\Nhave. They want to control every
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.51,0:32:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,everything.\NYeah. wanting to control others uh other
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.44,0:32:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,countries etc. calibrates about 180.\NSo certain organizations some of them
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.67,0:32:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,religious etc some political some\Ncombined the two uh want to conquer
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.15,0:32:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,other countries just to control them.\NThe desire to control others just for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.96,0:32:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the sake of control calibrates at 180.\NThey can try to convince themselves that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.91,0:32:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,they're saving your soul, but the\Nreality is they just want to control
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.55,0:32:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you, that you got to see things their\Nway. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.20,0:32:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let let go of the desire for applause.\NNobody's going to applaud. When you're
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.27,0:32:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,out in the woods and you save the life\Nof some little animal, there isn't any
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.91,0:32:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,applause. You see the little rabbit, you\Ntake it home, you nurse it, bring it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.32,0:32:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,back to health, it becomes a pet rabbit.\NUh so the thing is self-rewarding. You
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.20,0:33:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to look for extraneous\Nrewards. The reward is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.27,0:33:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,gratification of the desire to be of\Nassistance to that which is living.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.00,0:33:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I like be glad instead of mad.\NBe glad instead of mad that this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.32,0:33:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,incident has allowed you to realize\Nsomething about yourself and about life
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.48,0:33:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you didn't know before. So you're\Nglad. I'm glad that I realize that now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.76,0:33:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,about myself. Yeah. I'm glad I realize\Nthat I'm selfish. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.79,0:33:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize I was selfish before.\NDidn't want to put that much money in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.36,0:33:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the plate at church. No,\Nyou put a fiverr in the plate and then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.36,0:33:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you take three singles back out.\NAcceptance instead of resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.15,0:33:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,generous instead of stingy,\Ncandid with yourself, honest, openly
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.24,0:34:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,honest with yourself and others.\NYou have to learn how eventually to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.79,0:34:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,silence the mind and give up\Nthinkingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.88,0:34:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very difficult to do. How do you\Nsilence the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.83,0:34:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and give up thinking?\NWell, you do that by looking at the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.91,0:34:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,space around a thing instead of the\Nthing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.04,0:34:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I get this table as a generality\Nin a in a greater generality.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.32,0:34:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Do I have any thoughts about this table?\NNo, I don't have any thoughts about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.96,0:34:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It just is. So you can look at a thing\Nand let everything just be as it is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.07,0:34:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,without dis dissert dissertation in your\Nhead about what it is and what you
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.44,0:34:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,should do about it and should you move\Nit and shouldn't that be a different
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.32,0:34:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,color tablecloth etc etc. You can learn\Nhow to accept life on its own terms just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.04,0:35:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as it is. What's the point of doing\Nthat? Because then you live in a free
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.76,0:35:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,state all the time. You're going if it\Nrains, it rains. And if it doesn't rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.40,0:35:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't rain. And it's all the same\None way or the other. If it rains, you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.35,0:35:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,get to experience a rainy day. And if it\Ndoesn't rain, you get to experience a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.24,0:35:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,sunny day. So, you can't lose. If you\Naccept all possible alternatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.76,0:35:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,if you die poor, you you get put in a\Ncheap grave. And if you die rich, you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.32,0:35:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,get in a fancy cemetery.\NA fancy cemetery is better, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.92,0:35:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Acceptance instead of\Nresisting. Being generous instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.20,0:35:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stingy.\NHonest with yourself and with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.68,0:36:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Learn how to silence the mind. Give up\Nthinking. This means to look beyond it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.07,0:36:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look beyond it. To be forgiving instead\Nof vindictive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.96,0:36:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. All right. Work on your inner\Ntraits instead of the external ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.40,0:36:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Whether your shoes are shined is\Nsort of interesting, but not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.52,0:36:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your inner traits rather than your\Nexternal ones. It only takes a bone to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.28,0:36:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,make a dog happy.\Nrealize that it only takes a bone to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.80,0:36:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,make a dog happy.\NMy dog is happy all the time. I can hear
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.83,0:36:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,munch, munch, munch\Nall night long.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.72,0:36:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It only takes a dog, I mean a bone to\Nmake a dog happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.52,0:36:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And it only takes hiding the bone from\Nthe dog to make your wife happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.07,0:37:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That dog's going to chew on that bone\Nall night. Okay. Okay. All right. All
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.80,0:37:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,right.\NYou can hear the dog gnawing away on the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.04,0:37:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,bone. But after a while, I guess it does\Nget irritating. You're trying to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.72,0:37:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,sleep and the dog's going crunchy,\Ncrunchy, crunchy, crunchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.80,0:37:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But what we really mean by all this is\Nthe small things of life are fine. Small
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.52,0:37:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things of life are fine. I don't see\Nvery well. And so when I can't find my
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.92,0:37:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,cane, somebody says, "Here it is. Here's\Nyour cane here." I say, "Oh, God, thank
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.48,0:37:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you. Thank you." I don't know where the\Nthing was. And this the small things of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.88,0:37:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life make all the difference in the\Nworld. You know, uh there's a song used
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.00,0:37:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to be don't worry, be happy.\NDo you remember that song? Don't worry,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.68,0:37:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,be happy.\NAnybody remember that song?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.44,0:37:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. Don't worry, be happy. Make that\Nyour your s song and you can play that
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.48,0:37:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,in the background. While you're having\Nbreakfast, play don't worry, be happy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.11,0:38:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and you and you go to work humming as\Nyou drive along in the car. Choose
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.72,0:38:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual values and goals instead of\Nmaterial ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.92,0:38:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Like your ambition should be to be more\Nforgiving, to be more loving, to be more
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.68,0:38:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,generous,\Nuh to be of greater assistance to your
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.59,0:38:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,fellow man. All the things to make other\Nliving beings happy whether it's animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.64,0:38:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,human, vegetable. Yes.\NAll right. Choose spiritual friends and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.68,0:38:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,groups.\NGo from complete to complete. Oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.76,0:38:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Choosing spiritual friends and groups\Nmakes a difference because you tend to
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.40,0:38:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,become that with which you align. So if\Nyou align with a strong spiritual group,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.28,0:38:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you tend to become more and more that\Nway yourself. If you align align with
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.00,0:38:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the sort of intemperate, hostile,\Nviolent or relig hyper religious group,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.56,0:39:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you tend to become like them, sort of\Nspiteful and angry and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.40,0:39:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they actually have hate brigades. I\Nmean, I can't believe it. I see it on
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.76,0:39:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,television. And uh some poor guy who's\Nbeen shot overseas is being put in the
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.28,0:39:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,ground. And there's a hate group with\Nhate signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.68,0:39:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how you get to get heaven\Nwith a hate sign. You have to leave your
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.59,0:39:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,hate sign here to get into heaven. But\Nanyway, they do. They have hate groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.59,0:39:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's hysterical. Identify with the\Ngreater self rather than the small self.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.80,0:39:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept the limitations of humanness.\NAll right. So you say, how can so much
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.92,0:39:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,negativity and hostility?\NIt's because of the evolution of human
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.88,0:39:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness. Mankind does not evolve\Nto the angelic viewpoint to the angelic
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.52,0:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,point of being an angel. A human can\Nbecome more and more angelic and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:39:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually if you become sufficiently\Nangelic uh you don't need to come back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.83,0:40:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,here. However, you can if you wish and\Nuh I have met angels in bodies. I have
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.07,0:40:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,had angels stop and help me. I'm\Nthinking now about the guy who circled
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.11,0:40:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,around, circled around, came and got me\Nout of the fig out of the figure eight
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.68,0:40:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,highway and went and got it changed and\Nbrought back. That man was a saint. I
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.64,0:40:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,was a\N>> angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.20,0:40:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Huh? Angel. Yes. So, there are angels in\Nbodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.56,0:40:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something people don't really\Nknow. This man um I was on a clover leaf
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.07,0:40:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in my old truck and it broke down. There\NI am stuck on a clover leaf with a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.80,0:40:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,broken down truck. Oh god. In the middle\Nof nowhere. And this car pulled over and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.76,0:40:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the guy says, "You in trouble?" I said,\N"Yeah." Won't start. He says, "Here, let
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.56,0:40:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,me help you." Complete stranger. He got\Nout the lug lug wrench and took the lugs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.59,0:41:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,off the tire through the tire and all in\Nthe back of his pickup truck. He drove
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.76,0:41:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,half a mile away, went around to Clover\NLeaf, took took the truck tire to a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.52,0:41:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,repair station, had it repaired, came\Nback to Clover Leaf, came back to Clover
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.59,0:41:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Leaf, came back to me. It all took about\Nan hour and a half. Plus, he had to put
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.68,0:41:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,out the money to get the fire fixed.\NAnd of course, I gave him the money and
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.59,0:41:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I thanked him profusely.\NBut that's the first one I ever did the
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.76,0:41:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,arm on. uh that man he was an angel\Nangel in a human body. So there are
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.59,0:41:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there are actual angels within a human\Nbody. Uh we can evolve to that ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.83,0:41:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,by our own inner decision. Resist. Wow.\NYou can become an angel. You don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.88,0:41:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to croak\Nget run over.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:42:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can become angelic while you're\Nstill in a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.92,0:42:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NWe will become the first angelic group
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.48,0:42:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the history of mankind.\NA group of angels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.44,0:42:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,900 angels all at one place. Honey,\Nsome people in this group are already
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.64,0:42:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,angelic. Resist. They already got that\Nready. We already have angels sitting in
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.00,0:42:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the audience.\Nor $5. I'll introduce you to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.00,0:42:46.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No, not $5. A generous donation,\N>> huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.16,0:42:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Yeah. But, uh, that's a discovery we
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.48,0:42:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,made. I think it's pretty original with\Nus our work that um there are literally
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.48,0:43:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,angels\Nincarnate actually angels here living
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.44,0:43:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst us and radi radiating out\Ngoodness uh to mankind. So we are very
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.11,0:43:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,fortunate then in this group there are\Nangels that have returned to a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.40,0:43:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhhuh.\NOkay. Realize that life is a learning
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.76,0:43:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,curve. So you never have to be\Ndissatisfied with yourself because
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.64,0:43:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing as well as you can at this\Nmoment.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.48,0:43:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be doing better, you would\Nbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.80,0:43:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So being self-critical then is always\Narbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.64,0:43:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If you could be better, you would be.\NThe fact that you're not means you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.83,0:43:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,right now\Nbecause you haven't reached that goal
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.35,0:43:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yet. to be forgiving towards people who\Ncut in on you on traffic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.20,0:43:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh just as you're pulling up a car,\Npulls right in front of you and you have
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.64,0:44:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to be angelic not to curse the guy, you\Nknow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.04,0:44:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How many of you bless a person who pulls\Nin front of you in traffic?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.00,0:44:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Any hands?\NWell, this is a truthful group.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.11,0:44:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a truthful group. Uh it's hard to bless\Nthe person who pulls in in front of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.92,0:44:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but let's try that as a group\Nexperience.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.16,0:44:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Henceforth,\Nif somebody's rude to you in traffic and
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.24,0:44:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,pulls in in front of you, forgive them\Nfor being somewhat impaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.88,0:44:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they they they lack being gracious\Nand thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.80,0:44:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, maybe they got to go\Nto the bathroom. You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.76,0:44:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they're intoxicated as\Nbut we could practice in traffic. See,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.72,0:45:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,it's one thing to be spiritual on Sunday\Nmorning in church with all the hymns and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.40,0:45:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the music and all that.\NIt's another to be spiritual uh when
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.88,0:45:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you're in the middle of traffic.\NSo, that would be a good exercise we
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.68,0:45:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,could do as a group.\Nsaying that because you don't drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.56,0:45:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I was a cab driver for years. I\Ndrove a cab. I drove a truck. And uh All
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.72,0:45:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right, we could do that. Is it because\Nyou know being holy being all holy rolly
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.68,0:45:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in church is easy. The hymns and the\Nmusic and the organ and everybody's all
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.88,0:45:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so goody pie goody goody goody pie.\NNext time. All right. So, that could be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.44,0:45:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a practice. It could become our a\Npractice that we recommend. New people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.92,0:45:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,want to come in the group with them.\NYeah. Well, listen to what the rules
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.96,0:45:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are.\NYou have to be loving and gracious and
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.24,0:46:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving towards everybody in traffic.\NNo matter what they do, even if they
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.64,0:46:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pull pull up in front of you and slam\Nthe brake on,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.11,0:46:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you still have to be forgiving.\NThat's a good discipline, right? Anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.64,0:46:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can be forgiving in church and pious and\Nholy and all that rolly holy poly.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.20,0:46:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a destination. It's a\Ndirection. It's not a end point or
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.11,0:46:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no beginning and no end. Being\Nhappy is a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.24,0:46:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of being in this world to\Nmake the best of every situation to the
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.40,0:46:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,best that you can.\NThe spiritual lifestyle is reflective
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.72,0:46:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,versus impulsive.\NIt tends to be reflective. It sees how
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.83,0:46:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you were rude to that person in traffic\Nto get even with them. So, it's
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.07,0:46:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,reflective and it says that was pretty\Nrude on my part and at the time you did
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.83,0:47:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it, you justified it. But now when you\Nreflect on it, you say that really
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.31,0:47:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,wasn't a very gracious or\Num wonderful thing I did there.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.31,0:47:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you decide to do better. So\Nyou're constantly learning. A truly
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.31,0:47:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual person is constantly wor\Nlearning and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.76,0:47:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,get something out of everything. It's\Nreflective versus impulsive.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.35,0:47:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's thoughtful rather than critical.\NAnd it tends to be content instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.59,0:47:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,complaining.\NSo instead of complaining
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.64,0:47:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,about circumstances, what we do is we uh\Ncommit to a style of life that will
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.40,0:47:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,bring us closer and closer to our goal.\NUhu to be more and more self-forgiving
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.92,0:47:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of uh self uh critical.\NAnd you say, "Yeah, I was selfish right
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.72,0:48:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,there. I did take the last donut.\NI did take the last doughnut.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.07,0:48:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I went out for lunch. I did not take the\Nlast doughnut.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.76,0:48:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was gooder than them.\NAll right. So, we get a sense of what
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.16,0:48:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual means. It's a whole style.\NIt's a way of being in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.80,0:48:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of holding\Nvalues of yourself and the human
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.55,0:48:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,condition so that you're forgiving at\Nall times no matter how life goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.04,0:48:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That you did the best you could.\NYou can always attack yourself with the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.07,0:48:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,hypothetical and say, "Well, I could\Nhave done better." If you could have,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.96,0:48:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you would have.\NThe reason you don't do things is
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.59,0:48:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you really can't in a certain\Nstate of mind. It's only when you're in
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.68,0:49:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,a different state of mind that you can\Ndo it. So self-criticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.59,0:49:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,self-awareness is different than\Nself-criticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.20,0:49:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To be self-aware,\Nyou realize you could have been more
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.04,0:49:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,generous. Self-criticism is attacking\Nyourself for not being more generous. So
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.20,0:49:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easier, it's better to be spiritual\Nthan self-critical.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.20,0:49:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Life is a learning curve. All right. And\Ndo we have any more slides? Oh my
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.96,0:49:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,goodness.\NWhen in doubt, pray. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.35,0:49:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray.\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.16,0:49:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when when I think of the times in my\Nlife that I really prayed other than
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.76,0:49:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going to church and some great\Ncathedral, you know, that's a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.76,0:49:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,style of praying. Uh but when uh certain\Ndeath is looking you right in the eye,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.76,0:50:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that's when you really pray\Nwhen you're about to explode. So here's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.35,0:50:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,his mind floating next to the ship and\Nit's about to explode and he's a second
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.83,0:50:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and he says he was scared to death and\Nand I said to him, "Don't worry." I
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.76,0:50:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "It's not going to go off." And\Nbesides, even if it does, the only thing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.00,0:50:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that can happen is you'll die. And he\Nsaid, "Yeah, you're right."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.83,0:50:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly his fear left him.\NInstantly his fear left him. And uh it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.44,0:50:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,was huge mine that was starting to bump\Nagainst the side of the ship and we're
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.59,0:50:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to hold it away with this gaffing\Ngaff hook. And he says, "What if it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.76,0:50:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,explodes?" And I said, I said, "Well,\Nthen we die." He said, "Yeah, right. End
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.96,0:50:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,of fear. end of fear. When you accept\Nthe worst possible scenario, accept the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.44,0:50:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,worst possible scenario. That's another\Nway of uh getting rid of fear. Someday
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.59,0:50:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to be old and ugly and\Nblind. And I said, "Well, I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.83,0:51:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm at least halfway there, one eye\Nblind, and I ain't so good-looking as I
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.40,0:51:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,once was."\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.92,0:51:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,all right. So we seek through prayer and\Ncontemplation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.16,0:51:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh affirm that God is my source and my\Nsolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.80,0:51:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sing an inner voice. Now that's\Nsomething you don't read about, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.48,0:51:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pick an inner an inner song that pleases\Nyou. Uh, I I like what the uh
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.11,0:51:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,what the bank piper played today.\N>> And therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.52,0:51:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I could play his song that song within\Nmy mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.64,0:51:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Amazing Grace.\N>> Amazing Grace. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.64,0:51:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing Grace. And uh so that that's my\Nsong and especially on bag pipes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.92,0:51:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing grace is great. And I I have\Ngreat hopes that my funeral, the bag
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.59,0:52:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,piper will be playing Amazing Grace. If\Nnot, you'll hear about it later when you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.72,0:52:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,come over.\NOkay. Where was the bag piper for God's
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.35,0:52:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,sake?\NSing an inner song. I think Amazing
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.16,0:52:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Grace makes a beautiful song that that\Ntype of an uplifting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.59,0:52:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,purely spiritual. The Amazing Grace\Nitself is you know strictly uh spiritual
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.35,0:52:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,not religious spiritual. Okay. When\Nfeeling down say to yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.68,0:52:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,yours is the saddest story I've ever\Nheard.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.72,0:53:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Every once in a while, I give you little\Nclues about things to to write and put
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.96,0:53:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,on your mirror at home.\NThings that you can post in the corner
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.04,0:53:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of your mirror. And one of and this is\None of them. Yours is the saddest story
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.88,0:53:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I have ever heard.\NI've recommended that before. How many
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.40,0:53:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,people have yours is the saddest story\NI've ever heard on their on their
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.92,0:53:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mirror?\NHey, a few.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.68,0:53:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NBest thing to do is write it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.40,0:53:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours is is the saddest story I've ever\Nheard. You can underline is.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.80,0:53:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We already said it's the saddest story,\Nbut we should underline is. So after
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.72,0:53:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,this lecture, I want you to underline is\Nyours is the saddest story I've ever
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.48,0:54:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,heard. After the next lecture, we'll\Nunderline saddest
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.24,0:54:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is the sad. The was good, too. Is the\Nsaddest story I have ever. You got
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.52,0:54:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,underline ever.\NOkay. So, if you're poor, dumb, and
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.35,0:54:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ugly,\Nand hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.28,0:54:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody hates you.\NWhen we were a kid, we sang a song,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.55,0:54:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Everybody hates me. Guess I'll go eat\Nworms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.55,0:54:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody hates me. Guess I'll go eat\Nworms.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.24,0:54:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll go eat worms. That's another\Nhandy sign. So, you could change signs
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.20,0:54:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,during the moment so you don't get\Nbored. Like, here's the saddest story.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.48,0:55:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, I think I'll go and eat worms.\NI like even God feels sorry for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.07,0:55:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember that song, that story about\NWallaby? Everything goes wrong with his
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.59,0:55:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\N>> Yeah. He's poor and crippled. His
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.20,0:55:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,girlfriend leaves him. What is it, God?\NThe voice that comes out of the heaven
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.35,0:55:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,says, "I don't know either. Just\Nsomething about you pisses me off."
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.64,0:55:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I always like that story.\NOkay. Play the role of martyr and
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.11,0:55:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,justice collector. Play the role\Nhappiness is a sessation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.76,0:55:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray and contemplate.\NInsist on.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.16,0:56:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Okay.\N>> Why me? God, why you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.24,0:56:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,why do my slides slide all over?\NHowever, it doesn't bother me because I
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.24,0:56:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,am courageous and I will succeed no\Nmatter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.55,0:56:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> 79 up there around 74. All\Nright. When you're
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.72,0:56:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,down and out,\Nwhat's wrong is you fight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.55,0:56:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're down and out and you're\Nfighting being miserable and gloomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.72,0:57:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,insist on being miserable and gloomy.\NYour socks don't match.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.79,0:57:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a hole in one of them.\NAll your shirts are dirty and wrinkled.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.00,0:57:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The bed clothing fell on the floor\Nduring the night and the cat slept on
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.59,0:57:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NThese are all very handy things. I've
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.28,0:57:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,done them all.\NMake faces at yourself in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.64,0:57:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a good one.\NAnybody done that?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.16,0:57:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a good one. It's a great one.\NI mean, that that one you can't you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.64,0:57:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,can't beat make faces at yourself in the\Nmirror. You know, you look at the Z, you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.64,0:58:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,go.\NIt's hard to say depressed and visible
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.04,0:58:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when you make faces at yourself in the\Nmirror because the whole thing is I have
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.07,0:58:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,a hard time seeing myself in the mirror\Nnow. So, I have a hard time making faces
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.16,0:58:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,at myself in the mirror. I go like this\Nand I got the lights on myself trying
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.52,0:58:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to find some other way to\Ntorment myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.40,0:58:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Be grateful for the gift of life when\Neverything else settles down and you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.24,0:58:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,say, "Well, this is wrong. This is\Nwrong. These things have happened to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.92,0:58:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,me." Uh, but I've had the gift of life.\NAnd by living the gift of life in a
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.11,0:58:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,certain way, I have great hopes of uh\Nand looking forward to the afterlife.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.72,0:58:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So we live one day at a time and do the\Nbest we can and try to be your own best
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.64,0:58:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,friend.\NYes,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.92,0:59:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to choose whether you're going\Nto expand on a problem or diminish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.20,0:59:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to be a diminisher or an\Nexpander?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.44,0:59:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my god, we're out of eggs, you know,\Nor we're out of eggs, so we'll have
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.96,0:59:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,cereal. I mean, which which way you can\Nhave it either one way. Your day is
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.16,0:59:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,either ruined, we're all out eggs, or\Nyou can be happy, oh great, it'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.88,0:59:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have cereal for a change.\NClarify the confusion of your capital S
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.48,0:59:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,self with your social role. The self is\None thing. Your social role is another.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.31,0:59:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you can be in the higher self\Nand fulfill any social role without
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.55,0:59:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,changing identification.\NPlay the role of martyr or the injustice
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.48,0:59:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,collector.\NPlay the role of the hero. You have the
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.20,1:00:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,option to play the role of the victim or\Nthe hero. Play the role of morally
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.31,1:00:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,superior.\Ngoodter than you. Yep. Let go of being
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.52,1:00:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,an injustice collector. Oh, how unjust\Nit is. Hey, we watch that all day on
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.28,1:00:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,television. When it's a competition for\Ninjustice collectors, who's the most uh
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.52,1:00:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,martyed, you know, let go of being\Nprovocative to others. Every time you
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.55,1:00:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,see yourself getting provocative, you\Nsay, well, I may be triggered that. So,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.35,1:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,see yourself as the trigger of events.\NSo if you see an event happen in your
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.64,1:00:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,life that you're not happy about, ask\Nhow could I how could I have been the
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.00,1:00:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,trigger of that instead of blaming it on\Nthe other person. The other person's
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.55,1:00:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,impatient.\NSo you get mad at them for being
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.68,1:00:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,impatient. Then you realize you've been\Nkept them waiting for 10 minutes while
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.11,1:00:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you stood there and brush your teeth.\NStop pushing your luck. Avoid
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.44,1:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,catastrophe. Do not buy a house in the\Nflood plane.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.88,1:01:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,or on the edge of a mine mud cliff.\NEvery day there's a sad story. Went out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.72,1:01:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,all by himself in the jungle and got\Nlost.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.04,1:01:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Built a house on the edge of the\Nmudcliff and the mud cliff slid down and
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.96,1:01:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,along with your house.\NAsk yourself, who in the world would
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.11,1:01:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,build a house on the edge of a mud\Ncliff?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.72,1:01:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it all the time. You can drive\Ndown certain places in the California
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.04,1:01:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,coast. Sure enough, mud cliff house,\Nthe house is just edging itself closer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.59,1:01:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and closer to the edge.\NI'll say to Susan, I don't know how
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.68,1:01:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,people can live\Nthat close to a cliff in in the mud mud
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.52,1:02:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,cliffs. All right. Let go of being\Ninjustice collector. Let go of being
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.16,1:02:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,provocative. Stop pushing one's luck.\NAvoid catastrophe. People like to say
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.16,1:02:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they're they're not guilty. They're not\Nresponsible for it. Last week, I had a
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.96,1:02:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,doctor's appointment at 9 in the morning\Nand and the weather news said there was
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.04,1:02:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be what do you call it?\N>> Tornado.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.92,1:02:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Tornado. Right. The weather news said\Ntornado. Stay off route 89A.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.55,1:02:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of pushing our luck and then\Nblaming it on the weather, we just
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.72,1:02:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,cancelled the doctor's appointment.\NSimple enough, isn't it? But you can see
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.20,1:02:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,how many people would push it, keep the\Ndoctor's appointment, go off the road,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.83,1:02:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,be taken away by a a tow truck, and have\Na long sad story.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.68,1:02:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, don't keep pushing your luck. Avoid\Ncatastrophe.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.24,1:02:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not buy a house in the flood plane or\Nthe edge of a mud cliff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.28,1:02:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not win the lottery.\NYou ever see the story what happens to
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.55,1:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people's lives who win the lottery? The\Ndivorce rate is close to 100%. Murder,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.00,1:03:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,suicide, divorce, and uh surprisingly\Nhalf of them become bankrupt. How can
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.59,1:03:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you win the lottery and go bankrupt?\NThey they figured out how to do it. Do
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.83,1:03:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not ski in an avalanche area. These are\Nthe things that drive me crazy when I
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.03,1:03:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,watch the news. I can't stand watching\Nthe news.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.48,1:03:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Some idiot goes up to the avalanche area\Nand of course he almost dies. His skis
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.20,1:03:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,turn over and they got to send an\Nambulance
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.79,1:03:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and a plane to get him. Anybody who\Nwants to climb uh you know great big
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.68,1:03:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,climbers, I would make them post a bond\Nwith the state. You have to post a
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.79,1:03:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,$10,000 bond if you're going to climb\NMount Everest.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.88,1:03:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The 90 people who didn't make it have\Ncost the taxpayers a fortune.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.00,1:03:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to climb Mount Everest,\Nyou have to post a 10,000, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.55,1:04:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,million-doll bond with the parks\Ndepartment,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.24,1:04:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,obey the law, be polite to the police.\NAll these things seem so simple, and yet
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.59,1:04:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,every day on the news, I see people\Nmouth off to the police.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.79,1:04:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A cop is the last person I think I would\Nmouth off to.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.35,1:04:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop demonstrating.\NOh god, there's another one that gets
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.79,1:04:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,me. Every day you see demonstrators out\Nthere, they've got these big signs. Uh
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.96,1:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're going to demonstrate.\NAnd I always think, uh, who cares what
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.76,1:04:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you think?\NThey're pro this or they're against
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.03,1:04:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that. Why would anybody care what you\Nthink about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.24,1:04:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, they take it very seriously.\NStop demonstrating.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.20,1:04:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh it's a good idea to give up saving\Nthe world.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.72,1:05:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a really good idea to mind your own\Nbusiness.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.40,1:05:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't want to hear mind your\Nown business. It's my responsibility as
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.44,1:05:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,a citizen to get out there and\Ndemonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.11,1:05:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,my responsibility to get out there and\Ndemonstrate as a citizen.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.59,1:05:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NGive up being important. Oh, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.28,1:05:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Demonstrators. I think what goes on with\Ndemonstrators? Well, you get a feeling
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.20,1:05:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of being important.\NOh,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.20,1:05:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,another idea is pay your income taxes.\NThis never seems to dawn on the leaders
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.79,1:05:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of our country.\NThere isn't the bigname leader out there
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.11,1:05:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,who isn't behind in their income taxes.\NYou have ever noticed that? That's the
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.03,1:05:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,funniest thing. No matter who they are,\Nthe president's cabinet is made up of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.35,1:05:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,people who do not pay their income\Ntaxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:57.68,1:06:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the head of the tax department\Nhasn't paid his taxes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.35,1:06:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Lastly, smile and the world\Nsmiles with you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.07,1:06:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,uh cry and you cry alone.\NDedicate all your actions to God. Well,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.11,1:06:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens if you dedicate all your\Nactions to God is they automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.96,1:06:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,become changed and purified.\NIf you dedicate this demonstration to
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.35,1:06:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,God, you have to fool yourself into\Nthinking that your ego is divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.55,1:06:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because nobody's going to be pleased\Nabout your demonstrating except you.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.79,1:06:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so all of these steps that we uh talk\Nabout uh bring about an inner humility
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.20,1:06:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's the inner humility you stop\Nlistening to the voice of the ego and in
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.44,1:06:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,its place reigns the silence of God\Nand that God is all that is becomes
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.79,1:07:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,readily apparent without a single\Nthought. The divinity of all that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.16,1:07:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth.\NAll that exists is divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.16,1:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else except divinity exists.\NWithout divinity, there's no sky.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.31,1:07:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no earth. There's no table.\NThere's no Suzie. There's no audience.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.64,1:07:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that exists is divinity.\NPeriod.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.44,1:07:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing else exists except divinity.\NGod in the infinite number of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.59,1:07:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,expressions as people, as stage, as\Nsorne, as cane, as a cup of coffee.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.92,1:07:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to exist\Nis solely that of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.35,1:07:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What I just said is the truth. Zoe,\Nthat ought to do it for today.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.31,1:08:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that is\Neverything that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.07,1:08:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is an expression of divinity.\NDivinity as this cane, as this table, as
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.72,1:08:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,this Kleenex.\NThere's only two things. One is
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.15,1:08:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,existence and the other is\Nnon-existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.27,1:08:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists is divinity.\NThat makes life simple. Amen. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.08,1:08:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, boy.\NThank you, honey.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.35,1:08:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't see.
